body_html:
The warning: onnx optimizer is unable to parse input model... is an warning, not an error. It says the model is too old so the new optimizer is not able to do optimization.
re. the models in the onnx/models repo, which model did you run? I'm asking because most of them are converted from caffe2 and we have CI to make sure they are passing. The error you posted indicates the model exported from CNTK failed at the onnx checker's verification (meaning the model is invalid).

body:
The `warning: onnx optimizer is unable to parse input model...` is an warning, not an error. It says the model is too old so the new optimizer is not able to do optimization.
re. the models in the onnx/models repo, which model did you run? I'm asking because most of them are converted from caffe2 and we have CI to make sure they are passing. The error you posted indicates the model exported from CNTK failed at the onnx checker's verification (meaning the model is invalid).
